spans.text: THE Pencil's glowing Lines and vast Command , And Mankind
with thick Daubings all the Wall overspread
yawn through boundless Sky , Through the wide heavenly Arch , and trackless Road In Azure volumes the pure Aether flowed

the Painter had his Art displayed , With slower Hand , and Pencil more divine He blends each Colour , heightens every Line , Till various Forms the breathing Picture wears , And a mute Groupè of Images appears
Crouds of Angels over the Wall descend
every Corner of the Earth The scattered Dust is called to second Birth
the Sight ; Maimed of his Nose
the Sight ; Maimed of his Nose
the vital Ray Gives the first Motion to the panting Clay
The Godhead opening in his awful Face
! what mild Beams their gracious Influence shed , And how the pointed Radiance crowns his Head
an irksome Life of Pain : But Death and Hell subdued , the Deity Ascends Triumphant to his native Sky
the Form — alike the Look and Mien , Another WAINFLET in his Face is seen : When will , alas ! such spotless Worth be found
A stern Avenger , with relentless Mind , Waving a flamy Falchion ,
Vain are his Sighs and fruitless are his Tears , Vengeance and Justice
! with what various Charms the Piece is fraught , And with what pregnant Marks of Judgement wrought
